0%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1653x930+971+347/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F73%2F01%2Fe27b7eba421b877dde077841ed60%2Fcourtesy-of-prime-video-daniel-dae-kim-3000.jpg" class="img" alt="Daniel Dae Kim plays a spy who faked his own death in Butterfly." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Daniel Dae Kim plays a spy who faked his own death in &lt;em&gt;Butterfly&lt;/em&gt;.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Juhan Noh/Prime                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies: &lt;/strong&gt;In&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/03/nx-s1-5525863/the-thursday-murder-club-cozies-up-to-murder" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Thursday Murder Club&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;a group of retirees gather to research cold cases to pass the time — until a real murder and a plucky new member show up on their doorstep.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; Daniel Dae Kim stars in &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/03/nx-s1-5526919/butterfly-spy-thriller-daniel-dae-kim" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Butterfly&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as a former U.S. government spy who comes out of hiding to save his long-lost daughter from her life as an assassin.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/02/nx-s1-5522363/new-books-this-week" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;To the Moon and Back&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;follows Steph Harper, who aspires to become NASA's first Cherokee astronaut. Before she can achieve her dreams, she must escape an abusive parent and navigate her youth spent on a reservation while experiencing a queer coming of age.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music: &lt;/strong&gt;Artist Nourished by Time's new album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/01/nx-s1-5518288/nourished-by-time-passionate-ones-profile" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Passionate Ones&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, is a not-so-quiet, yearning and romantic expression that nothing can stand in the way of pursuing love.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓ Quiz:&lt;/strong&gt; I have been bested this week. I got seven out of the 11 questions right. I know you can do better! &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/05/g-s1-86970/google-trump-florida-fox-stephen-king-news-quiz" target="_blank"&gt;Test your memory&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-87193" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2376;         --source-height: 1337;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2376x1337+0+123/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F5e%2Fd9%2F7cf219b64960844218dc62a8751f%2Fanisimova2-getty.jpg" class="img" alt="Amanda Anisimova of the United States celebrates after defeating Naomi Osaka of Japan in three sets during their women&amp;#039;s singles semifinal match on Sept. 5, 2025, in the Queens borough of New York City." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Amanda Anisimova of the United States celebrates after defeating Naomi Osaka of Japan in three sets during their women's singles semifinal match on Sept. 5, 2025, in the Queens borough of New York City.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sarah Stier/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;American Amanda Anisimova defeated Naomi Osaka of Japan early today in the U.S. Open semifinals. She is expected to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/04/nx-s1-5528663/naomi-osaka-amanda-anisimova-us-open-semifinals" target="_blank"&gt;compete in her first U.S. Open finals&lt;/a&gt; tomorrow.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Giorgio Armani, the founder of the Italian luxury fashion house Armani, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/04/1110320559/giorgio-armani-dead" target="_blank"&gt;died yesterday in Milan&lt;/a&gt; at age 91. His designs had a goal of highlighting the body as a work of art.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Susan Stamberg, one of NPR's "founding mothers," is retiring after over 50 years behind the mic. &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5508910:x" target="_blank"&gt;shares a tribute to her legacy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
