ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0d%2F7d%2F95ea76034c60b7998de6d298b18d%2Ffarflungpostcard-horz-feng.jpg" class="img" alt="FarFlungPostcard_Horz-Feng.jpg" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;This week, the Far-Flung Postcards series takes readers to a Christian church built by ancient Arab people over 1,500 years ago in the Negev desert. NPR's Emily Feng &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/27/g-s1-85311/negev-desert-nabataeans-archaeology" target="_blank"&gt;visited the site&lt;/a&gt; earlier this month.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Today, the U.S. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/28/nx-s1-5519361/de-minimis-rule-tariffs-consumers-imports-trump" target="_blank"&gt;ends the "de minimis" trade exemption&lt;/a&gt; that allows individuals to avoid import fees for small shipments. This will affect around 4 million packages processed each day.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Julian Wachner, a once prominent conductor and composer in New York City, has been &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/28/nx-s1-5509937/conductor-julian-wachner-arrested" target="_blank"&gt;charged in Indiana with possessing&lt;/a&gt; child sexual abuse material and cocaine. Until his arrest, he was working as a fourth-grade teacher.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
